1
00:00:07,563 --> 00:00:09,063
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:11,647 --> 00:00:13,063
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:15,272 --> 00:00:17,230
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:19,355 --> 00:00:21,355
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:23,438 --> 00:00:25,272
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:30,063 --> 00:00:34,938
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 8)

7
00:00:37,772 --> 00:00:38,938
Oh!

8
00:00:39,063 --> 00:00:40,063
What?

9
00:00:40,188 --> 00:00:41,938
Wait, is my dad really here?

10
00:00:42,063 --> 00:00:44,522
Yes, it's His Majesty the Emperor.

11
00:00:44,647 --> 00:00:45,647
Contact him! Hurry!

12
00:00:45,730 --> 00:00:47,313
But Prince, I can't get this to connect.

13
00:00:47,438 --> 00:00:50,678
I think it's probably because of the device
interference with the communications on Earth.

14
00:00:50,772 --> 00:00:53,063
Hachi! Are you messing with me?

15
00:00:53,188 --> 00:00:54,313
Prince, it's true!

16
00:00:54,438 --> 00:00:55,647
You know Hachi can't lie.

17
00:00:55,772 --> 00:00:59,272
His Majesty clearly said that
he entered our solar system.

18
00:00:59,938 --> 00:01:01,230
Did he say anything else?

19
00:01:01,355 --> 00:01:02,475
It's just my opinion, but...

20
00:01:02,563 --> 00:01:04,438
I think His Majesty has brought a fleet.

21
00:01:04,563 --> 00:01:06,022
A fleet?

22
00:01:06,147 --> 00:01:08,563
Is he here to conquer Earth?

23
00:01:08,688 --> 00:01:10,813
His Majesty, invading Earth?

24
00:01:10,938 --> 00:01:12,355
Stop talking nonsense.

25
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:15,105
You guys can play your royal games.

26
00:01:15,522 --> 00:01:17,397
I'm going to find my brother.

27
00:01:17,522 --> 00:01:18,813
I'm coming too.

28
00:01:19,897 --> 00:01:20,897
Wait!

29
00:01:21,022 --> 00:01:21,855
I wanna go too.

30
00:01:21,980 --> 00:01:23,539
Our Princess should probably be there too.

31
00:01:23,563 --> 00:01:24,272
Boss!

32
00:01:24,397 --> 00:01:27,355
Okay, where are we going to find Woo-hyuk?

33
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:28,938
We have to check everywhere.

34
00:01:29,063 --> 00:01:32,272
Okay, wait. I know someone
who might know where he is.

35
00:01:32,397 --> 00:01:33,980
Would you like to go see him?

36
00:01:44,147 --> 00:01:45,813
(Return)

37
00:02:33,355 --> 00:02:35,230
Ugh... damn it...

38
00:02:38,897 --> 00:02:40,188
Soon-nam.

39
00:02:40,313 --> 00:02:42,188
You're surprisingly sharp.

40
00:02:43,022 --> 00:02:44,563
Is it this way?

41
00:02:45,188 --> 00:02:45,980
Officer Shin.

42
00:02:46,105 --> 00:02:47,688
I mean, he's not much of a talker,

43
00:02:47,813 --> 00:02:49,563
but he's incredibly smart.

44
00:02:59,147 --> 00:03:01,980
Let's go together! Huh?

45
00:03:04,813 --> 00:03:06,522
What's wrong?

46
00:03:06,647 --> 00:03:07,938
I didn't even call for you.

47
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:11,813
We're here to say that the Emperor has already
entered the solar system with his fleet.

48
00:03:12,397 --> 00:03:13,230
W-what?

49
00:03:13,355 --> 00:03:17,063
Looks like we need to change the plan.

50
00:03:17,188 --> 00:03:18,313
C-change the plan?

51
00:03:18,438 --> 00:03:21,272
We don't have time to slowly
harvest Earth's energy anymore.

52
00:03:21,397 --> 00:03:23,230
We don't have time for that.

53
00:03:23,897 --> 00:03:25,577
We need to extract all the energy at once,

54
00:03:25,647 --> 00:03:26,980
and leave Earth immediately.

55
00:03:27,105 --> 00:03:28,980
Are you... are you insane?!

56
00:03:29,397 --> 00:03:31,647
That will kill every living thing on Earth!

57
00:03:31,772 --> 00:03:32,772
What about our money?

58
00:03:32,897 --> 00:03:34,938
What about our investors?

59
00:03:49,272 --> 00:03:50,355
Forget it, let's just go.

60
00:04:01,897 --> 00:04:02,980
Good grief.

61
00:04:06,147 --> 00:04:07,188
Wait a second.

62
00:04:07,313 --> 00:04:08,938
Why are we heading up?

63
00:04:09,063 --> 00:04:11,105
Can't you tell? We're catching the culprit.

64
00:04:11,230 --> 00:04:12,230
We're on our way up now.

65
00:04:12,313 --> 00:04:14,063
He's got a gun!

66
00:04:14,438 --> 00:04:16,313
I have a gun too, don't I?

67
00:04:16,438 --> 00:04:19,105
Isn't that... the memory-erasing gun?

68
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:20,105
That's right.

69
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:22,063
Isn't that broken?

70
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:26,980
Huh?

71
00:04:29,105 --> 00:04:30,647
It works perfectly fine.

72
00:04:34,272 --> 00:04:35,438
Hey, this guy...

73
00:04:35,563 --> 00:04:36,581
Is he really going to be okay?

74
00:04:36,605 --> 00:04:38,022
He'll wake up in a few hours.

75
00:04:38,147 --> 00:04:39,522
I calculated the shot perfectly.

76
00:04:39,647 --> 00:04:40,730
His memory will be fine.

77
00:04:40,855 --> 00:04:42,355
Alright, let's go catch the culprit.

78
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,313
Are we just going to leave him here?

79
00:04:44,438 --> 00:04:45,706
It's safer for him to sleep here.

80
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:48,230
- No way...
- He wouldn't be any help anyway.

81
00:04:52,313 --> 00:04:54,022
You're cold-blooded.

82
00:04:54,147 --> 00:04:57,105
Poor alien, you've drained him dry.

83
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:59,022
Vampire boss.

84
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:05,022
Do you know what this is?

85
00:05:05,147 --> 00:05:07,522
A self-destruct device.

86
00:05:07,647 --> 00:05:10,355
Boom, boom, boom.

87
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:12,480
If I press this, you're all finished.

88
00:05:12,605 --> 00:05:14,272
The harvester will blow up too.

89
00:05:20,397 --> 00:05:21,397
Then press it.

90
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,688
Oh...

91
00:05:28,563 --> 00:05:29,813
Coward.

92
00:05:30,855 --> 00:05:32,563
You think I won't press it?

93
00:05:32,688 --> 00:05:34,438
You're really underestimating me.

94
00:05:34,563 --> 00:05:36,022
Press it!

95
00:05:52,355 --> 00:05:55,313
Oh, Chairman, you're so cute, aren't you?

96
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,480
Chairman.

97
00:05:57,605 --> 00:05:59,813
You've worked hard all this time.

98
00:05:59,938 --> 00:06:01,313
Rest in peace.

99
00:06:02,563 --> 00:06:05,938
Wait... before you go, I
have something to say.

100
00:06:06,063 --> 00:06:08,522
Chairman, you remember the plan, right?

101
00:06:10,238 --> 00:06:13,980
It started when I gave you the
blueprints for the energy harvester.

102
00:06:14,105 --> 00:06:15,147
Remember?

103
00:06:16,730 --> 00:06:21,688
Actually... I stole them from the palace.

104
00:06:22,647 --> 00:06:24,272
The truth is...

105
00:06:25,063 --> 00:06:29,355
I used to be a palace guard.

106
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:31,480
This is getting interesting.

107
00:06:31,605 --> 00:06:34,772
Why not just give it to him?
What's with the proposal?

108
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:39,313
Chairman, I really admire you.

109
00:06:39,438 --> 00:06:42,105
W-well then...

110
00:06:43,188 --> 00:06:45,355
No... no! Don't shoot!

111
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,938
- Don't shoot...
- No!

112
00:06:47,063 --> 00:06:48,730
Don't shoot!

113
00:06:53,355 --> 00:06:55,355
That should keep us from being suspected.

114
00:07:16,188 --> 00:07:18,230
Are we really going the right way?

115
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:20,855
Didn't Hachi say it was this way?

116
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:24,175
Why trust him? Hachi
gets lost all the time.

117
00:07:24,313 --> 00:07:28,022
I can sense various signals of
interference coming from that direction.

118
00:07:28,147 --> 00:07:29,563
Interfering with communications...

119
00:07:29,688 --> 00:07:30,855
And landing on Earth?

120
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:33,563
Yes, if my senses are correct.

121
00:07:34,063 --> 00:07:35,105
A river!

122
00:07:36,438 --> 00:07:37,647
That's a river!

123
00:07:37,772 --> 00:07:39,730
Such precious water...

124
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,473
There's so much of it... it's amazing.

125
00:07:45,522 --> 00:07:48,772
Precious water? Are you from a desert?

126
00:07:48,897 --> 00:07:50,397
A desert?

127
00:07:53,897 --> 00:07:55,855
Any place without Wooju...

128
00:07:56,522 --> 00:07:57,938
is a desert to me.

129
00:08:04,063 --> 00:08:05,688
What are you talking about?

130
00:08:13,605 --> 00:08:15,147
Wooju.

131
00:08:15,813 --> 00:08:18,813
To me...

132
00:08:20,938 --> 00:08:22,855
you are as precious as water.

133
00:08:30,855 --> 00:08:32,688
Wow! Look at that.

134
00:08:32,813 --> 00:08:34,813
People are riding bicycles!

135
00:08:34,938 --> 00:08:36,397
I want to ride a bicycle.

136
00:08:36,522 --> 00:08:37,522
Me too.

137
00:08:37,605 --> 00:08:42,105
What? You've never ridden a bike before?

138
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,730
Let's ride that.

139
00:08:45,647 --> 00:08:48,147
How poor are you guys?
You've never seen a bike?

140
00:09:07,063 --> 00:09:09,147
Um... is this a suicide?

141
00:09:09,272 --> 00:09:11,855
Doesn't look like it. Why
would they commit suicide?

142
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:15,105
Hey, is alien blood blue?

143
00:09:15,223 --> 00:09:17,282
It can be red, orange, yellow,
green, blue, indigo, or violet.

144
00:09:17,313 --> 00:09:18,393
Every species is different.

145
00:09:18,438 --> 00:09:19,188
If it were suicide,

146
00:09:19,313 --> 00:09:21,123
they wouldn't hold a
gun to their own forehead.

147
00:09:21,147 --> 00:09:22,272
Exactly.

148
00:09:22,397 --> 00:09:23,957
This was staged to look like a suicide.

149
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:27,022
Wait... who could it be?

150
00:09:30,647 --> 00:09:31,688
I'm taking this.

151
00:09:31,813 --> 00:09:32,980
Hey, you can't.

152
00:09:33,105 --> 00:09:34,147
This is evidence.

153
00:09:34,272 --> 00:09:34,938
I can't?

154
00:09:35,063 --> 00:09:37,647
No, it has to be kept
at the police station.

155
00:09:37,772 --> 00:09:39,647
No matter how much you want it,

156
00:09:39,772 --> 00:09:41,772
you shouldn't touch a
dead person's belongings.

157
00:09:41,897 --> 00:09:44,522
I know whose ring this is.

158
00:09:45,105 --> 00:09:46,188
Whose?

159
00:09:46,313 --> 00:09:48,188
It's Prince Raon's mother's.

160
00:09:48,938 --> 00:09:50,188
Really?

161
00:09:50,313 --> 00:09:52,522
Yes, I'll make sure to deliver it for you.

162
00:09:52,647 --> 00:09:56,647
Even so, we have to wait until
the police investigation is over.

163
00:09:57,438 --> 00:09:58,230
Senior.

164
00:09:58,355 --> 00:10:02,522
This looks like a suicide
note in the envelope, but...

165
00:10:02,647 --> 00:10:05,688
What is this? Alien language?

166
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:08,647
Hmm... this is...

167
00:10:08,772 --> 00:10:09,813
What does it say?

168
00:10:09,938 --> 00:10:11,897
He says he poisoned the Queen.

169
00:10:12,022 --> 00:10:14,063
And it says after coming to Earth,

170
00:10:14,188 --> 00:10:16,081
he killed the baker couple
who were close to the King.

171
00:10:16,105 --> 00:10:19,605
Wait, who is the Queen?
And who are the bakers...

172
00:10:19,730 --> 00:10:20,730
No...

173
00:10:20,855 --> 00:10:22,688
Ah! You scared me! A zombie!

174
00:10:22,813 --> 00:10:23,397
What is this?

175
00:10:23,522 --> 00:10:24,188
Zombie! Zombie!

176
00:10:24,313 --> 00:10:27,022
What? Are you awake?

177
00:10:29,022 --> 00:10:31,563
Hey, are you awake?

178
00:10:34,938 --> 00:10:36,938
My head... ah...

179
00:10:37,063 --> 00:10:38,438
Are you okay?

180
00:10:39,522 --> 00:10:42,980
Wait... how is he still alive?
He was shot in the forehead.

181
00:10:46,647 --> 00:10:49,522
No! I pressed this button.

182
00:10:49,647 --> 00:10:51,105
What is this button?

183
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:52,813
It's a bit complicated.

184
00:10:52,937 --> 00:10:55,413
It's a device that prevents death
even if you're shot by an Earth gun.

185
00:10:55,438 --> 00:10:57,414
I pretended it was a self-destruct
button when I pressed it.

186
00:10:57,438 --> 00:11:00,313
Do you know who the culprit is?

187
00:11:00,438 --> 00:11:04,063
It's that guy... Secretary
Lee is the culprit!

188
00:11:04,188 --> 00:11:06,522
Isn't he working with them? Why?

189
00:11:06,647 --> 00:11:09,730
They're going to destroy
Earth, and I don't want that!

190
00:11:09,855 --> 00:11:11,147
Who would believe that?

191
00:11:11,272 --> 00:11:13,355
Exactly, you even
locked us in the basement!

192
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:16,040
I'll explain everything later.
Please, trust me one more time...

193
00:11:16,105 --> 00:11:18,355
Mr. Wooju might know something!

194
00:11:19,397 --> 00:11:20,230
Wooju is in danger.

195
00:11:20,355 --> 00:11:21,105
Hurry, we have to find Wooju.

196
00:11:21,230 --> 00:11:22,855
Hey... let's go...

197
00:11:23,772 --> 00:11:26,105
No! Let's go together, together...

198
00:11:26,230 --> 00:11:29,813
My head hurts... my head
hurts, let's go together!

199
00:11:34,605 --> 00:11:35,188
Is this the place?

200
00:11:35,313 --> 00:11:36,563
Yeah.

201
00:11:37,647 --> 00:11:40,147
Is hyung here?

202
00:11:52,105 --> 00:11:53,480
Go, go, go!

203
00:12:32,188 --> 00:12:33,438
Impressive.

204
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:36,480
I didn't think you'd
actually find this place.

205
00:12:36,605 --> 00:12:37,772
That's enough.

206
00:12:39,313 --> 00:12:39,980
Stop it.

207
00:12:40,105 --> 00:12:41,730
Why?

208
00:12:42,813 --> 00:12:44,647
If it's money you want,
I can give it to you.

209
00:12:46,855 --> 00:12:49,313
You sound exactly like the Queen.

210
00:12:49,438 --> 00:12:51,248
Your mother said the
exact same thing back then.

211
00:12:51,272 --> 00:12:53,897
She said she'd pay whatever it took.

212
00:12:54,438 --> 00:12:55,772
My mother?

213
00:12:55,897 --> 00:12:59,980
Prince, that guy... wasn't he
the Queen's bodyguard?

214
00:13:00,105 --> 00:13:01,813
I think he was.

215
00:13:11,188 --> 00:13:12,855
It was you...

216
00:13:14,397 --> 00:13:16,022
You killed my mother?

217
00:13:19,938 --> 00:13:23,355
That's right. No point in hiding it now.

218
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,813
That's right.

219
00:13:25,563 --> 00:13:29,147
I poisoned the bread
made by the royal baker.

220
00:13:30,147 --> 00:13:31,897
You poisoned my mother...!

221
00:13:32,022 --> 00:13:33,397
Damn it...

222
00:13:35,848 --> 00:13:36,991
You didn't just kill my mother...

223
00:13:37,022 --> 00:13:40,897
You framed Wooju's father for it too...

224
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:45,272
Then you came to Earth
and killed Wooju's parents...!

225
00:13:47,522 --> 00:13:50,438
Raon... I have no idea
what you're talking about.

226
00:13:52,147 --> 00:13:53,897
What are you guys saying...

227
00:13:54,522 --> 00:13:56,147
What is going on?!

228
00:13:59,272 --> 00:14:00,772
This jerk...

229
00:14:04,147 --> 00:14:09,147
He's the one who killed
my mother and your parents!

230
00:14:09,272 --> 00:14:10,272
Is all of this true?

231
00:14:11,522 --> 00:14:13,188
That's all in the past!

232
00:14:13,313 --> 00:14:16,063
The past? You call this the past?

233
00:14:17,105 --> 00:14:18,438
Damn it.

234
00:14:27,313 --> 00:14:28,688
Wooju!

235
00:14:29,938 --> 00:14:31,230
Wooju!

236
00:14:38,355 --> 00:14:39,730
No...

237
00:14:41,313 --> 00:14:42,772
Ah!

238
00:14:44,063 --> 00:14:45,522
Damn it...

239
00:14:46,855 --> 00:14:49,772
Wooju, hang in there...

240
00:14:54,688 --> 00:14:56,022
Wooju!

241
00:14:59,813 --> 00:15:01,147
Just hold on!

242
00:15:01,272 --> 00:15:02,605
Wooju!

243
00:15:17,147 --> 00:15:18,563
Get out of my way!

244
00:15:24,313 --> 00:15:25,713
Where are you in such a rush to go?

245
00:15:25,772 --> 00:15:27,730
Get lost, you fucker!

246
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:34,313
Come out here! You bastard!

247
00:15:34,438 --> 00:15:36,522
You are under arrest for murder.

248
00:15:36,647 --> 00:15:38,397
You have the right to remain silent.

249
00:15:38,522 --> 00:15:39,980
Let go of me! Get your hands off me!

250
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:40,980
Let go! Damn it...

251
00:15:41,105 --> 00:15:42,105
Stay still, you punk...

252
00:15:42,147 --> 00:15:44,230
I'm going to shut down
the energy harvester.

253
00:15:48,397 --> 00:15:50,397
(Wooju Bakery)

254
00:15:52,147 --> 00:15:53,772
It's all over now.

255
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:57,272
What about this alien?

256
00:15:57,397 --> 00:16:00,063
- We can't take him to the station.
- Just stay still, damn it.

257
00:16:44,855 --> 00:16:47,188
What happened to that guy with the knife?

258
00:16:48,438 --> 00:16:51,897
What are you talking about?
You must've been dreaming.

259
00:16:52,438 --> 00:16:54,730
I swear I got stabbed
for you and collapsed...

260
00:16:59,647 --> 00:17:05,438
That's strange... Was it just a dream?

261
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:12,605
Why would you take a
knife for me in a dream?

262
00:17:12,730 --> 00:17:17,147
Because I don't want to
lose... a person important to me.

263
00:17:19,522 --> 00:17:21,230
Am I important to you?

264
00:17:23,022 --> 00:17:26,855
Of course. But I think I
find you more important...

265
00:17:26,980 --> 00:17:28,730
Than you value me.

266
00:17:31,397 --> 00:17:33,063
What's that supposed to mean?

267
00:17:33,188 --> 00:17:39,147
Never mind... Why am I suddenly so sleepy?

268
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,980
Get some rest.

269
00:18:09,313 --> 00:18:12,272
Why did you use the memory eraser on Wooju?

270
00:18:12,397 --> 00:18:14,563
He never believed in aliens to begin with.

271
00:18:14,688 --> 00:18:17,730
If he knew he had alien blood in him...

272
00:18:17,855 --> 00:18:19,563
He'd be completely overwhelmed.

273
00:18:19,688 --> 00:18:21,855
I didn't wipe his memory completely.

274
00:18:21,980 --> 00:18:27,147
I just made it feel like a hazy dream.

275
00:18:29,063 --> 00:18:33,980
Is it really okay to keep it from him?

276
00:18:35,063 --> 00:18:39,147
Wooju used to be so gloomy.

277
00:18:39,272 --> 00:18:41,105
He's only recently started to open up.

278
00:18:41,230 --> 00:18:43,855
I don't want him to go back
to having a hard time, Raon.

279
00:18:49,063 --> 00:18:51,397
I want to be by Wooju's side
even through the tough times.

280
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:58,980
Isn't it more important to make
the person you love happy?

281
00:19:02,730 --> 00:19:08,688
Even if Wooju finds out everything...

282
00:19:09,938 --> 00:19:11,688
I'm confident I can make him happy.

283
00:19:11,813 --> 00:19:13,063
Raon.

284
00:19:13,813 --> 00:19:15,230
Here.

285
00:19:18,647 --> 00:19:19,480
What is this?

286
00:19:19,605 --> 00:19:21,063
It's your mother's keepsake.

287
00:19:21,188 --> 00:19:24,188
It's still being held as police evidence.

288
00:19:24,313 --> 00:19:25,980
I'll be going now.

289
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:55,480
I truly hope you find happiness, Wooju.

290
00:20:23,147 --> 00:20:24,563
The Emperor!?

291
00:20:25,605 --> 00:20:29,897
Hachi, I'll be landing near you soon.

292
00:20:30,022 --> 00:20:31,313
Prepare for my arrival.

293
00:20:31,438 --> 00:20:34,272
Yes, I will... Wait, what?

294
00:20:34,397 --> 00:20:36,313
But how did you know the coordinates?

295
00:20:36,438 --> 00:20:40,772
Hmph... Princess Q told me everything.

296
00:20:40,897 --> 00:20:42,230
Be ready.

297
00:20:42,813 --> 00:20:46,313
We're in trouble... we're in big trouble!

298
00:20:46,438 --> 00:20:49,813
Hachi! Is he coming here?

299
00:20:49,938 --> 00:20:51,688
Boss! Prince!

300
00:20:52,605 --> 00:20:54,897
- Wait... Hachi, wait!
- Prince!

301
00:20:55,147 --> 00:20:58,230
Boss! Prince! His Majesty's about to land!

302
00:20:59,313 --> 00:21:00,313
What?!

303
00:21:00,397 --> 00:21:01,230
Who's coming?

304
00:21:01,355 --> 00:21:04,063
Look at that window! Right there!

305
00:21:06,605 --> 00:21:07,355
Right there!

306
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,938
Oh my god.

307
00:21:09,063 --> 00:21:11,397
Look! Over there! Let's go.

308
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,563
Where are we going now?

309
00:21:14,688 --> 00:21:16,980
To the place where they
make bread at Wooju Bakery.

310
00:21:17,105 --> 00:21:18,563
Can this thing even make it there?

311
00:21:19,647 --> 00:21:23,438
And isn't this thing... still broken?

312
00:21:23,563 --> 00:21:24,813
It's fixed.

313
00:21:26,397 --> 00:21:27,477
This car is acting weird...

314
00:21:27,563 --> 00:21:29,313
I told you, it's a spaceship.

315
00:22:00,647 --> 00:22:02,980
Mr. Kim was able to leave the Earth.

316
00:22:03,105 --> 00:22:05,897
He finally returned to his family.

317
00:22:06,022 --> 00:22:09,105
Of course, some chose to stay.

318
00:22:09,980 --> 00:22:11,563
You ask why?

319
00:22:12,313 --> 00:22:13,397
I love this one!

320
00:22:13,522 --> 00:22:16,230
Some stay because they love Earth's food.

321
00:22:16,355 --> 00:22:17,772
How much for this?

322
00:22:18,522 --> 00:22:21,438
Others stay because
they love Earth's music.

323
00:22:24,438 --> 00:22:26,980
Why did you bring these guys here?

324
00:22:27,105 --> 00:22:28,865
We couldn't take them
to the police station.

325
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:30,230
No one would believe us anyway.

326
00:22:30,355 --> 00:22:32,289
Didn't you say someone from Wooju's side
would come to pick them up soon?

327
00:22:32,313 --> 00:22:34,230
Let's just keep them here for now.

328
00:22:34,355 --> 00:22:38,355
By the way, are you two dating?

329
00:22:40,022 --> 00:22:41,938
Who said we're dating?

330
00:22:43,647 --> 00:22:45,563
And some people...

331
00:22:46,897 --> 00:22:48,522
stay for love.
